&lt;h2 id="application-settings"&gt;Application settings&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are my settings for the applications you’re most likely interested in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="visual-studio-code"&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Press &lt;code&gt;CMD + SHIFT + P&lt;/code&gt;, then search “Install code command in PATH” and click to start using &lt;code&gt;code .&lt;/code&gt; to open files from the terminal in VSCode.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VS Code has a feature called &lt;a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/settings-sync" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Settings Sync&lt;/a&gt; which you can use sync your VSCode settings, keybindings and extensions with your new device. It makes the transition from one machine to another seamless.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="extensions"&gt;Extensions&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=sdras.night-owl" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Night Owl&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=bungcip.better-toml" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Better TOML&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
